description: Test the voltage on both sides of the diode in the load module when the relay is closed to check if the diode is conducting or if it is blocking current (possibly due to reverse polarity or diode fault)., outcome='The diode anode measures 0.3592 V and the cathode 0.0003 V, indicating the diode is forward biased and conducting. The Load Input Cable (+) is at 0.3592 V and Load Input Cable (−) is at 0.0003 V. No polarity inversion is detected; voltages are consistent with standard circuit orientation.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=60.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> control module output terminal (toward load module),
description: Measure the voltage at the control module output terminals (where they connect to the load module) during the lamp's intended ON state to confirm whether a full 12V is present there. This will help determine if voltage is being properly delivered from the control module to the load module., outcome='The measured voltage at the Control Output Cable (+) is 0.3592 V, and at the Control Output Cable (−) is 0.0003 V, both with respect to ground. There is not a full 12V present at the control module output terminals during the intended ON state.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
